Hello,
My team needs help tuning our PID controllers. To tune our PID we are using the TalonSRX PID tuning instead of the frc PIDController class.
Our code is available here

We have already tuned the PID F value by using this link
We have been unable to tune the V and A values that are needed for motion magic, as we are 1. unsure if we are using a Position-Closed loop mode or not, and 2. unsure how to set a target in Phoenix Tuner X. We would prefer to use only phoenix tuner x but will be able to use code if needed.
We are missing V, A, P, D, and I.
We are using 8 TalonSRX’s, with the drive motors being cims and their encoder being cimcoders. For the steer motors we are using PG27 with the hall effect rs775 encoders.
Thanks
